 higher AF-induced hemodynamic\nvariability lead to a coronary perfusion impairment exceeding 90-110 bpm in AF.\nMoreover, it is found that coronary perfusion pressure (CPP) is no longer a\ngood measure of the myocardial perfusion for HR higher than 90 bpm.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Apr 2019 12:31:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-17"}
