from high to low services and collapse. Where public services are\ninsufficient, community adaptation improves water security and resilience to\nvarying degrees. Our results highlight the need for resilience thinking in the\ngovernance of urban water systems under global change pressures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Apr 2019 15:21:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Aug 2019 22:30:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-08"}
